message.content:
1. Can you provide specific evidence or documentation that supports the belief that the remains of Travis, Bowie, and Crockett were possibly buried at Mission San Francisco de la Espada?
2. Are there historical records or archaeological findings that directly link the burial location of the Alamo dead to the sarcophagus in question?
3. Is there any verifiable information confirming the handling and re-interment of the remains believed to belong to some of the Alamo defenders discovered at the Cathedral of San Fernando in 1936?
